This code is provided 'AS IS' and any warranties are disclaimed.


3.Functional restrictions

- PHY address is assumed as 1. The other addresses are not supported.
- VLAN functions are not supported.
- Priority queue functions are not supported.
- TBI is not supported. (MII or GMII)


4.Considerable Configuration Keywords

- NSC says that TXEARLY(TxDrth), TXFLTH and TXMXDMA restrict each other. 
    FIFOsize(8KB) - TXEARLY >= TXFLTH > TXMXDMA
  Be careful if you want to modify these parameters.

- Set RXAIRL=YES, if you want to use the netbios(NETBEUI) protocol.
  Tcp/ip and/or netbios over tcp/ip are not subject to this parameter.


