7.History

ver.1.09 - 12/24, 2005.
- Bugfix: Multiple receive descriptors per a frame can work now.

ver.1.08 - 12/17, 2005.
- 1 new keyword, IRQ15OVR, was added.

ver.1.07 - 11/15, 2005.
- Workaround for Virtual PC.

ver.1.06 - 4/1, 2004.
- PHY medium initialize, speed detection code were modified.
- The format of MAXFRAME keyword was modified.

ver.1.05 - 12/29, 2003.
- Bus master enable and memory space enable bits in PCI command register 
   are scanned at the initial time.

ver.1.04 - 11/24, 2003.
- Bugfix: TXQUEUE can be specified larger than 28, on that condition 
   Transmit queues initialization failure has occured.

ver.1.03 - 11/18, 2003.
- Power Management capability in PCI register is scanned at initial time.
- EARLYMEMINIT=TRUE in config.sys was supported.

ver.1.02 - 7/11, 2003.
- Bugfix: Transmit Data Type 2, GDT selector, is permitted.
- Rx queue logic is modified. (RxRelease before returning from RxChain)
- Short time I/O delay to access PHY registers was inserted.(see note)
- Rejection of TCP checksum failure is enabled.

ver.1.01 - 12/18, 2002.
- 3 new configuration keywords, RXAEP, RXARP, RXAIRL, were added.

ver.1.00 - 12/8, 2002.
-  Initial release.


